snippet.textDisplay:
Hi there! That enclosure is far too small for any species of animal, especially hamsters which require 540 square inches of unbroken floor space. They can run 5-10 miles a night and it is not fair to keep them in an enclosure far below the minimum. Many people are uneducated on proper hamster care and, while a bad thing, is not usually the owner’s fault. Please take the time to read about proper hamster care because their quality of life will be improved greatly. Yes, they can live in a small enclosure for their whole life, but they will not be as happy as they should be. They can survive, but they will not thrive.

Also, just a note, hamsters require about 6-11” (hamster burrow a lot so 11” is best IMHO) bedding at the deepest point and they can not use wire wheels (wire wheels cause bumble foot).

I appreciate the sentiment of treating your animals to new things to stimulate their brains and enrich their lives but please also read about their basic care requirements. Both matter!

Thank you for reading! Please be aware of proper hamster care 🐹
